⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Dinner Table
node AHX · AHX · ⟦The Dinner Table:AHX:83ee99⟧

WHO   — The Dinner Table — where the hate is taught
WHAT  — The origin made ordinary: the film's insistence that hate is not born but taught, in kitchens, over dinner, by people you love.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film roots the whole tragedy in the most domestic possible scene.
HOW   — By showing prejudice passed from father to son as offhand table-talk, and erupting later into open cruelty.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am a family dinner. The most dangerous thing in this whole film happened at me, said casually, to a child.

